Title: The Jackal
Original title: The Jackal
Released: 1997
Genre: Crime thriller, thriller, adventure
Directed by: Michael Caton-Jones / Michael Caton-Jones
Starring: Bruce Willis, Richard Gere, Sidney Poitier, Diane Venora, Mathilda May, JK Simmons, Richard Laynbek, John Cunningham, Jack Black, Tess Harper
About the film: "The Jackal" - a nickname. Beneath it lies one of the most elusive criminals international scale, hired killer, performing the most complex jobs of those "employers" who are able to pay a lot of money. Once in Moscow night club was a joint operation of the American special services and Russian police, was killed by one of the leaders of the Russian mafia, the brother of the deceased appealed to the Jackal and made an "order".
This information is leaked to the FBI. It became clear that the purpose of the killer is someone "at the top" of the White House. To stop the Jackal, the Americans released from prison Irish terrorist Declan Malkuina, whose own accounts with the Jackal and that - the only one! - Knows the assassin in the face
